------------------------------------------------------------------------
Documentation included with the Release

Information on unpacking, installing and initial testing of O-Plan
is provided the "INSTALL" file.

The following documents are provided in the release iamge in
PostScript form in subdirectories of the "documentation" directory

  - User Guide
  - TF Manual

Additional documentation is included in the directory "source/doc".

Information on interfacing other systems to O-Plan is provided in
the following files:

  source/doc/ta-interface
  source/doc/ta-interface-quick-reference

Information on using a Web browser to provide a "COA evaluation matrix"
interface to O-Plan can be found in:

  source/doc/http-mode

------------------------------------------------------------------------
Support Information and Materials

Information and materials which support the release can be found at 
http://www.aiai.ed.ac.uk/~oplan/release

------------------------------------------------------------------------
Documents Describing O-Plan

Tate, A., Drabble, B. and Dalton, J. (1996)
O-Plan: a Knowledge-Based Planner and its Application to Logistics
- in Advanced Planning Technology, Morgan Kaufmann, (Tate, A. ed.),
AAAI Press, May 1996.
http://www.aiai.ed.ac.uk/~oplan/documents/1996/96-arpi-oplan-and-logistics.ps

A collection of papers on the O-Plan system was provided in the
following Technical Report.  These papers are all available via
http://www.aiai.ed.ac.uk/~oplan/documents/index.html

Tate, A., Drabble, B. and Dalton, J.  An Engineer's Approach to the
Application of Knowledge Based Planning and Scheduling Techniques to
Logistics, USAF Rome Laboratory Technical Report RL-TR-95-235,
December 1995.

Demonstration domain descriptions in O-Plan's Task Formalism (TF)
can be found via http://www.aiai.ed.ac.uk/~oplan/release/tf

PlanWorld Viewers based on AutoCAD as released with version 2.3 are
provided in http://www.aiai.ed.ac.uk/~oplan/release/2.3/ac

